    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-09T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-09T20:00:00-05:00" n="825"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d825">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">681.003/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-09T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 9, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Your 14, January 7, 7 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d825fn12">Not printed.</note>
                    as a basis for your conversation with the Ministry regarding Moroccan situation,
                    in order to avoid possible ambiguity with respect to the expiration of the
                    Franco-British accord, it is suggested that you eliminate the second paragraph
                    on page 4 of the Department’s instruction 669, December 18,<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d825fn13">
                        <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_876">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 876</ref>.</note> and substitute for
                    (1) on same page the second sentence at top of page 2 of the note enclosed<note
                        n="14" xml:id="d825fn14">Not printed; the sentence referred to is quoted in
                        second paragraph of telegram No. 5, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> with the above instruction from Ponsot to Laboulaye which refers to the
                    expiration of the period of 30 years for which the maintenance of the principle
                    of commercial liberty was contemplated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
